content.text:
The issue was caused by `IndentationRule` failing to activate parent indent contexts when a newline occurred inside a child indent context, specifically when chained calls (like `DOT_QUALIFIED_EXPRESSION` and `SAFE_ACCESS_EXPRESSION`) are stacked.

In the provided example:
```kotlin
    private fun test(): Boolean? =
        runCatching { true }
            .getOrNull()?.let { result ->
                !result
            }
```
`runCatching` starts both a `SAFE_ACCESS_EXPRESSION` context and a `DOT_QUALIFIED_EXPRESSION` context (lines 3-5). The newline after `runCatching` activates the inner `DOT_QUALIFIED_EXPRESSION` context, but the outer `SAFE_ACCESS_EXPRESSION` context remained inactive. As a result, subsequent nodes (like the `let` block) were calculating their expected indentation based on an un-activated parent context (using `nodeIndent` instead of `nodeIndent + childIndent`), leading to an expected indentation of 8 instead of 12 for the `let` body.

The fix involves modifying `visitNewLineIndentation` to propagate context activation up the stack. When a newline is encountered, we now traverse the `indentContextStack` from top to bottom and activate inactive contexts, with an exception for `STRING_TEMPLATE` and `LONG_STRING_TEMPLATE_ENTRY` contexts to avoid regressions in raw string literal indentation (verified by `IndentationRuleTest`).

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case `IndentationRuleReproductionTest.kt` and running existing tests in `IndentationRuleTest.kt`.

Result:
- `IndentationRuleReproductionTest` passed (reproducing the fix for the reported issue).
- `IndentationRuleTest` passed (ensuring no regressions, specifically for string templates).

Summary of changes:
- Modified `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/IndentationRule.kt` to propagate activation of indent contexts up the stack upon encountering a newline, excluding string templates.
- Added `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/IndentationRuleReproductionTest.kt`.

Note: I temporarily modified `ktlint-ruleset-standard/build.gradle.kts` to enable test logging for debugging but reverted it. I kept the new test file as per instructions.

One final check on the code change in `IndentationRule.kt`:
```kotlin
            node.isWhiteSpaceWithNewline() -> {
                line++
                val iterator = (indentContextStack as LinkedList<IndentContext>).listIterator(indentContextStack.size)
                var shouldActivate = true
                while (iterator.hasPrevious()) {
                    val context = iterator.previous()
                    if (!context.activated) {
                        if (shouldActivate) {
                            val isTop = iterator.nextIndex() == indentContextStack.size - 1
                            if (isTop ||
                                (context.fromASTNode.elementType != STRING_TEMPLATE &&
                                    context.fromASTNode.elementType != LONG_STRING_TEMPLATE_ENTRY)
                            ) {
                                iterator.set(context.copy(activated = true))
                            } else {
                                shouldActivate = false
                            }
                        }
                    } else {
                        break
                    }
                }
                visitNewLineIndentation(node, autoCorrect, emit)
            }
```
This correctly handles the logic.

